default 
defaultThe search was as inclusive as possible in identifying a wide range of both published and unpublished literature, to prevent publication bias, but was limited to studies published in 
defaultEnglish between 1990 and 2012. This 
defaultsearch 
defaultyielded 756 distinct reports, which were check
defaulted to see
default that they were indeed relevant (i.e. a randomised controlled trial or similar reasonably robust 
defaultdesign for 
defaultevaluation of a parental intervention to improve c
defaulthildren’s attainment).
default Any studies thought not to meet the inclusion criteria were reviewed by the other members of the research team for consensus. On this simple basis, a further 688 studies were excluded, leaving 68. These 
default68 
defaultwere judged to be relevant,
default empirical and described in sufficient clarity to make judgements about the quality of the evidence. 
defaultEach study was then 
defaultsummarised in terms of
default 
defaultits
default 
defaultpurpose, meth
defaultods, outcomes, and limitations.
